   1:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp **** /**
   2:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * fsr_calibrate.cpp â€” FSR min/max pressure calibrator on ADC1
   3:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * Daisy Seed
   4:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  *
   5:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * Reads an FSR on A1 (ADC1 / D16 / pin 23). After capturing a brief idle
   6:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * baseline, waits for the first touch to begin the 15-second calibration
   7:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * window. Vary your pressure across the full range during that window â€”
   8:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * release, press lightly, press as hard as you'll ever play, etc.
   9:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  *
  10:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * At the end prints both extremes AND speaks them through the audio output
  11:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * ("minimum: 1 2 3 4 5 ; maximum: 6 7 8 9 0"). Speech samples are 8 kHz mono
  12:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * 8-bit PCM baked from macOS `say -v Samantha`, upsampled 6Ă— for the 48 kHz
  13:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * audio engine.
  14:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  *
  15:tools/fsr_calibrate.cpp ****  * Open `screen /dev/tty.usbmodem* 115200` to view text output.
